# 📱 Mobile Application Development (Flutter)

A comprehensive, 3-level course designed to take you from beginner to advanced Flutter developer.

---

## 👨‍🏫 Course Incharge
**Sahil Khimani**

---

## 🧑‍🎓 Certification
✅ Certificate will be awarded upon completion of **each module**.

---

## 📘 Module 1: Basic Level – Foundations of Flutter & Dart
**Duration:** 10 Weeks  
**Objective:** Learn Dart fundamentals and basic Flutter UI development.

### Week-by-Week Breakdown
- **Week 1:**  
  - What is Flutter? Why use it?  
  - Installing SDK & IDE (VS Code, Android Studio)  
  - Dart basics: variables, data types, functions  

- **Week 2–3:**  
  - Control flow (if/else, loops, switch)  
  - Collections: List, Set, Map  
  - OOP: Classes and Objects  
  - Hands-on with DartPad  

- **Week 4:**  
  - Practice sessions & test  

- **Week 5–6:**  
  - Flutter architecture: Widget tree  
  - Stateless vs Stateful widgets  
  - Text, Image, Container, Row, Column widgets  

- **Week 7:**  
  - First App: Counter  
  - Hot reload, debugging  
  - Buttons and inputs  

- **Week 8:**  
  - Navigation between screens  
  - Data passing & Material Design  

- **Week 9:**  
  - GitHub introduction and sessions  

- **Week 10:**  
  - Final Project

---

## 📗 Module 2: Intermediate Level
**Duration:** 8 Weeks  
**Objective:** Build real-world apps using APIs, forms, and storage.

### Week-by-Week Breakdown
- **Week 1:**  
  - State: setState vs lifted state  
  - Introduction to Provider  

- **Week 2–3:**  
  - Forms & TextFormField  
  - Input validation  
  - Practice exercises  

- **Week 4:**  
  - HTTP requests  
  - JSON parsing  
  - API integration  

- **Week 5:**  
  - ListView.builder  
  - ScrollControllers  
  - Pull-to-refresh  

- **Week 6–7:**  
  - SharedPreferences  
  - sqflite database  
  - CRUD operations  

- **Week 8:**  
  - Project Week

---

## 📕 Module 3: Advanced Level – Professional App Development
**Duration:** 8 Weeks  
**Objective:** Build production-ready apps using Firebase, state management, animations & architecture.

### Week-by-Week Breakdown
- **Week 1:**  
  - Provider (advanced), Riverpod/Bloc overview  
  - Managing large app states  

- **Week 2:**  
  - Firebase setup  
  - Auth, Firestore  
  - Login/registration, real-time DB  

- **Week 3:**  
  - Tween, AnimatedBuilder, Hero  
  - Custom widgets  

- **Week 4:**  
  - Debugging performance  
  - Code splitting, image caching  

- **Week 5:**  
  - Advanced Navigation  
  - Named routes, deep linking  

- **Week 6:**  
  - MVC vs MVVM vs Clean Architecture  
  - get_it (DI), mockito for testing  

- **Week 7–8:**  
  - Final Project & Presentation
